  "texts": [
    "After imposing this bound their largest allowed values are O(10 -11), see Table 2.",
    "Muon conversion in nuclei provides the most stringent constraint, as displayed in Fig. 20.",
    "The largest allowed value for B(B s → τ + µ -) and B( B0 → K * 0 τ + µ -) are reduced to O(10 -13), see Table 2.",
    "A summary of the impact of the lepton decays on B(B s → τ + µ -) and B( B0 → K * 0 τ + µ -) is in Fig. 22, where we plot their correlation when subsequent constraints from LFV charged lepton decay modes are imposed.",
    "It is instructive to examine the mutual impact of different LFV lepton decays."
